---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="MUDdown — Markdown-Powered MUDs">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>The Future of MUDs is <span>Markdown</span></h2>
      <p>
        MUDdown reimagines text adventures for the modern era. Rooms are documents.
        Links are commands. AI agents are first-class players. And it all runs everywhere.
      </p>
      <div class="cta">
        <a href="/play" class="primary">Play Now</a>
        <a href="/spec" class="secondary">Read the Spec</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="features">
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h3><span class="icon">📝</span> Markdown-Native</h3>
        <p>
          Room descriptions, combat logs, and dialogue are structured Markdown.
          Readable as plain text, beautifully rendered in browsers, parseable by machines.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h3><span class="icon">🌐</span> Multi-Platform</h3>
        <p>
          Play in a browser, on your phone, or in a terminal. One protocol,
          every surface. WebSocket transport with graceful degradation.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h3><span class="icon">🤖</span> AI-First</h3>
        <p>
          Game state exposed via structured schemas compatible with LLM tool-calling
          and Model Context Protocol. AI agents can play or assist seamlessly.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h3><span class="icon">🔗</span> Federated</h3>
        <p>
          Servers link realms together. Walk between worlds through dimensional portals.
          Your identity travels across servers.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h3><span class="icon">♿</span> Accessible by Design</h3>
        <p>
          Screenreader-first architecture. Semantic Markdown with ARIA-mapped container blocks.
          Text adventures should be for everyone.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h3><span class="icon">🧩</span> Extensible</h3>
        <p>
          Custom container blocks, plugin architecture, and a typed wire protocol.
          Build crafting systems, procedural worlds, or anything you imagine.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="example container">
    <h2>What MUDdown Looks Like</h2>
    <pre><code>:::room&#123;id="iron-gate" region="northkeep" lighting="dim"&#125;
# The Iron Gate

A massive portcullis of blackened iron bars the passage north.
The mechanism is **rusted**, but you notice
[fresh oil on the gears](cmd:examine gears).

## Exits
- [North](go:north) *(blocked)*
- [South](go:south) — Courtyard
- [Up](go:up) — Guard Tower

## Present
- [@Tharion](player:tharion) is here, studying the mechanism.
- A [sleeping guard](npc:guard-7) slumps against the wall.
:::</code></pre>
    <p style="color: var(--text-dim); margin-top: 1rem;">
      It's just Markdown. Any renderer displays it. MUDdown-aware clients make the links clickable,
      the blocks interactive, and the whole thing playable.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
